   galloprovincialis, Crassostrea gigas, and Ruditapes sp. presented very
   low concentrations of DA in the Ebro Delta bays, despite 113 alert
   situations according to Pseudo-nitzschia spp. abundances and the high
   number of shellfish samples analyzed. The origin of DA in Catalan
