   scallops maintained in 100 ng ml(-1) dissolved DA for 18 days. No
   significant effect of exposure to DA was observed on feeding rate (on
   microalgae), shell valve activity (shell clatter), righting response, or
   the secretion of byssus threads. However, negative impacts on growth
   rate and survival were found for scallops exposed to DA-spiked feed.
